1
00:00:39,767 --> 00:00:41,833
<i> Dad, we have a visitor.</i>

2
00:00:41,967 --> 00:00:42,667
<i> Dad?</i>

3
00:00:42,800 --> 00:00:43,700
<i> Coleen?</i>

4
00:00:43,833 --> 00:00:45,200
<i> Dad!</i>

5
00:00:45,333 --> 00:00:46,400
<i> Dad!</i>

6
00:00:46,533 --> 00:00:48,600
<i> I've done you so much wrong.</i>

7
00:00:48,733 --> 00:00:50,500
<i>My dear, I hope
you can forgive me.</i>

8
00:00:50,633 --> 00:00:52,933
<i>I'm glad to have met you
in person.</i>

9
00:00:53,067 --> 00:00:54,233
<i> Me, too, Coleen.</i>

10
00:00:54,367 --> 00:00:55,633
<i> And Coleen, Mom...</i>

11
00:00:55,767 --> 00:00:59,133
<i>I'm sure she's hiding some crime
she doesn't want us to discover.</i>

12
00:00:59,267 --> 00:01:00,867
<i>- Andrea.
- The person she wants to see</i>

13
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:02,433
<i> is here in the Philippines.</i>

14
00:01:02,567 --> 00:01:03,800
<i> Where else would she go?</i>

15
00:01:03,933 --> 00:01:04,733
<i> Jessica!</i>

16
00:01:04,867 --> 00:01:06,100
<i>You're trying to run away
from me?</i>

17
00:01:06,233 --> 00:01:07,133
<i> Come here!</i>

18
00:01:07,300 --> 00:01:08,833
<i> Hazel!</i>

19
00:01:08,967 --> 00:01:09,933
<i>- Jessica!
- Hazel!</i>

20
00:01:10,067 --> 00:01:11,467
<i>- They escaped from me.
- Is it my fault</i>

21
00:01:11,600 --> 00:01:12,600
<i> that you're dumb?</i>

22
00:01:12,733 --> 00:01:13,933
<i> I know they're with Felma.</i>

23
00:01:14,067 --> 00:01:16,233
<i>So you better give me
Felma's address.</i>

24
00:01:16,367 --> 00:01:17,467
<i> What do you think I am? Crazy?</i>

25
00:01:17,600 --> 00:01:19,467
<i>Please help me get them
through the back.</i>

26
00:01:19,600 --> 00:01:20,633
<i> Hurry up!</i>

27
00:01:20,767 --> 00:01:21,933
<i> Your brother's here.</i>

28
00:01:22,067 --> 00:01:23,133
<i>So that's why you wouldn't
tell us where we were going.</i>

29
00:01:23,267 --> 00:01:24,933
<i>This is where you were planning
to take us all along.</i>

30
00:01:25,067 --> 00:01:25,867
<i> Is Coleen home already?</i>

31
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:27,067
<i> Coleen's here!</i>

32
00:01:27,200 --> 00:01:28,733
<i>- Where did you go?
- Where else? To her father!</i>

33
00:01:28,867 --> 00:01:29,433
<i> Yes.</i>

34
00:01:29,567 --> 00:01:30,967
<i> I went to see dad.</i>

35
00:01:31,100 --> 00:01:32,133
<i>We've already discussed this,
haven't we?</i>

36
00:01:32,267 --> 00:01:33,667
<i>We agreed you wouldn't call
your father anymore!</i>

37
00:01:33,800 --> 00:01:35,400
<i>Because you knew
this would happen!</i>

38
00:01:35,533 --> 00:01:36,600
<i> Trouble!</i>

39
00:01:36,733 --> 00:01:38,867
<i>Just meeting with me
already causes a big issue.</i>

40
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:40,833
<i>What more if they find out
we're here?</i>

41
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:42,633
<i>We need to get out of here
right away.</i>

42
00:01:42,767 --> 00:01:44,667
<i> Dad, please don't leave.</i>

43
00:01:44,800 --> 00:01:46,600
<i>I still want to spend time
with you and Jessica.</i>

44
00:01:46,733 --> 00:01:47,933
<i> I agree with dad.</i>

45
00:01:48,067 --> 00:01:51,200
<i>We don't want to risk your
relationship with your family.</i>

46
00:02:01,433 --> 00:02:02,167
All right.

47
00:02:04,600 --> 00:02:06,567
I'll let you go.

48
00:02:07,567 --> 00:02:11,433
But can we all eat
together first?

49
00:02:11,567 --> 00:02:12,867
After mom leaves.

50
00:02:15,700 --> 00:02:16,967
Please, Dad?

51
00:02:26,867 --> 00:02:27,633
Didang.

52
00:02:27,767 --> 00:02:28,400
- Didang?
- Ma'am.

53
00:02:28,533 --> 00:02:29,500
Yes?

54
00:02:31,033 --> 00:02:33,367
Can you check on Coleen?

55
00:02:33,500 --> 00:02:34,733
Sure, Ma'am.

56
00:02:34,867 --> 00:02:36,333
Let me cook this first, okay?

57
00:02:36,467 --> 00:02:37,067
Wait.

58
00:02:37,200 --> 00:02:38,000
You're going to cook?

59
00:02:38,133 --> 00:02:40,000
There's still a lot of food.
Look.

60
00:02:42,667 --> 00:02:45,633
Ma'am, this is Coleen's request.

61
00:02:45,767 --> 00:02:47,533
Why is it too much?

62
00:02:47,700 --> 00:02:48,600
Oh, well...

63
00:02:48,733 --> 00:02:52,567
she said she didn't eat
anything last night.

64
00:02:52,700 --> 00:02:56,167
And I'm planning to eat
the leftovers for lunch.

65
00:03:00,500 --> 00:03:01,933
Didang?

66
00:03:02,067 --> 00:03:04,067
Ma'am?

67
00:03:04,200 --> 00:03:05,800
Why do you look so tense?

68
00:03:05,933 --> 00:03:07,533
Me? Tense? No way.

69
00:03:09,233 --> 00:03:13,400
Well, last night I clearly
heard you and Coleen arguing

70
00:03:13,533 --> 00:03:15,033
in the room.

71
00:03:17,100 --> 00:03:20,833
I'm glad that she got
to see her father.

72
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:26,900
But I have to protect my family.

73
00:03:27,033 --> 00:03:30,667
I don't want our family
to fall apart.

74
00:03:30,800 --> 00:03:34,000
Manuel and Coleen shouldn't
see each other anymore.

75
00:03:47,400 --> 00:03:49,400
This woman is crazy!

76
00:03:49,533 --> 00:03:53,200
125 messages, 80 missed calls.

77
00:03:53,333 --> 00:03:55,133
Hazel's driving me nuts!

78
00:03:55,300 --> 00:03:57,067
She behaves like a troll.

79
00:03:57,200 --> 00:03:58,933
Call Manuel, will you?

80
00:03:59,067 --> 00:04:00,867
I already gave you the address,
didn't I?

81
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:02,467
They're not there.

82
00:04:02,600 --> 00:04:04,100
Call him and ask where he is.

83
00:04:04,233 --> 00:04:05,467
No. I don't want to.

84
00:04:05,600 --> 00:04:06,467
And why not?

85
00:04:06,600 --> 00:04:07,467
I said I don't want to!

86
00:04:07,600 --> 00:04:09,033
Oh, is that so?

87
00:04:09,167 --> 00:04:10,733
Hey!

88
00:04:10,867 --> 00:04:11,933
You can't call him.

89
00:04:12,067 --> 00:04:14,367
You don't know my password.

90
00:04:14,500 --> 00:04:15,667
It's my birthday, you idiot!

91
00:04:15,800 --> 00:04:17,300
You're so obsessed with me!

92
00:04:21,867 --> 00:04:23,733
Uncle Abel's calling, Dad.

93
00:04:28,133 --> 00:04:29,467
<i> - Hello, Bro.
-</i> Hello, Manuel!

94
00:04:29,600 --> 00:04:30,100
Where are you?

95
00:04:32,367 --> 00:04:34,667
Oh, yeah? Can't even
answer now, huh?

96
00:04:34,800 --> 00:04:35,867
Impressive!

97
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:38,833
<i>Can you please stop
bothering my friend?</i>

98
00:04:38,967 --> 00:04:41,967
Just go back to Canada,
to your burden of a wife!

99
00:04:42,100 --> 00:04:43,533
Got it?

100
00:04:43,667 --> 00:04:45,000
Paz, wait, hold on.

101
00:04:45,133 --> 00:04:46,367
Let me explain.

102
00:04:46,500 --> 00:04:48,767
Don't tell me to hold on,
Manuel!

103
00:04:48,900 --> 00:04:49,733
You're unbelievable!

104
00:04:49,867 --> 00:04:51,267
Two decades.

105
00:04:51,400 --> 00:04:53,100
For two decades, you've been
making life miserable

106
00:04:53,233 --> 00:04:54,533
for your family.

107
00:04:54,667 --> 00:04:55,167
<i> Okay?</i>

108
00:04:55,300 --> 00:04:56,533
<i> For heaven's sake!</i>

109
00:04:56,667 --> 00:04:57,700
<i> Just stop causing trouble.</i>

110
00:04:57,833 --> 00:04:58,467
Just leave already.

111
00:04:58,600 --> 00:04:59,433
Stop!

112
00:04:59,567 --> 00:05:00,300
That's enough, Paz!

113
00:05:00,433 --> 00:05:01,833
No, I'm not stopping!

114
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:04,667
I want to teach your so-called
BFF a lesson first, okay?

115
00:05:04,800 --> 00:05:06,867
<i> No guts, and no heart!</i>

116
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:08,200
For heaven's sake.

117
00:05:08,333 --> 00:05:10,033
This bastard, this liar,

118
00:05:10,167 --> 00:05:11,700
is coming back into the lives
of Felma and her children again.

119
00:05:11,833 --> 00:05:13,233
Enough already!

120
00:05:13,367 --> 00:05:14,000
What's the deal?

121
00:05:14,133 --> 00:05:15,367
Felma isn't even being bothered!

122
00:05:15,500 --> 00:05:17,167
<i>What do you mean he's
not bothering Felma?</i>

123
00:05:17,300 --> 00:05:18,500
Do you know what
that jerk is doing?

124
00:05:18,633 --> 00:05:24,600
He's using his kid with Hazel
to beg for favors from Felma!

125
00:05:24,733 --> 00:05:26,967
<i> Isn't that manipulation?</i>

126
00:05:27,100 --> 00:05:28,033
Do you understand me?

127
00:05:28,167 --> 00:05:29,167
You've got no shame left!

128
00:05:29,300 --> 00:05:31,300
That face of yours,
I'm going to slap it right off!

129
00:05:31,433 --> 00:05:32,133
What an ugly face you've got.

130
00:05:32,267 --> 00:05:33,200
Stop it already!

131
00:05:33,333 --> 00:05:34,200
You!

132
00:05:34,367 --> 00:05:35,100
You're not a man.

133
00:05:35,233 --> 00:05:36,233
You've got no balls!

134
00:05:36,367 --> 00:05:37,200
That's enough!

135
00:05:37,333 --> 00:05:38,033
<i> No!</i>

136
00:05:38,167 --> 00:05:39,033
<i> I want coffee.</i>

137
00:05:39,167 --> 00:05:39,933
<i> I'm thirsty.</i>

138
00:05:40,067 --> 00:05:41,000
<i> Stop it!</i>

139
00:05:50,933 --> 00:05:56,167
Dad, please don't mind
what Auntie Paz said.

140
00:05:56,300 --> 00:05:58,300
What she said is true.

141
00:05:58,433 --> 00:06:00,700
That's why we really
need to leave.

142
00:06:03,033 --> 00:06:03,933
There's mom!

143
00:06:07,367 --> 00:06:10,367
She hasn't left yet!

144
00:06:10,500 --> 00:06:13,400
Ma'am, let me do the cooking.

145
00:06:13,533 --> 00:06:14,200
I got this.

146
00:06:14,333 --> 00:06:16,400
I know what my youngest likes.

147
00:06:16,533 --> 00:06:18,133
She wants it toasted,

148
00:06:18,267 --> 00:06:20,867
and she likes it when the
inside's nice and crispy.

149
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:24,267
Even I like how you cook it,
Ma'am.

150
00:06:28,433 --> 00:06:29,767
I'll be right back, Ma'am.

151
00:06:37,867 --> 00:06:39,833
<i> Here's your favorite.</i>

152
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:45,000
<i> That's why I love you so much.</i>

153
00:06:45,133 --> 00:06:46,567
<i> Of course, I love you, too.</i>

154
00:07:07,900 --> 00:07:10,033
Dad. Coleen.

155
00:07:10,167 --> 00:07:11,600
Be quiet.

156
00:07:11,733 --> 00:07:12,800
What's happening?

157
00:07:16,567 --> 00:07:17,533
Dad...

158
00:07:19,067 --> 00:07:20,300
what's with the smile?

159
00:07:22,533 --> 00:07:26,067
I saw Felma smiling again.

160
00:07:26,200 --> 00:07:28,533
The Felma I used to know.

161
00:07:28,667 --> 00:07:31,967
Not the cold Felma we met with.

162
00:07:33,300 --> 00:07:35,867
Mom met with you?

163
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:37,733
Yes, Coleen.

164
00:07:37,867 --> 00:07:39,567
We haven't told you yet,
have we?

165
00:07:41,067 --> 00:07:44,367
Actually, I asked for some help.

166
00:07:44,500 --> 00:07:45,767
And she was willing.

167
00:07:48,767 --> 00:07:51,767
That means, mom still
can't neglect you.

168
00:07:51,900 --> 00:07:54,000
Wait, that means...

169
00:07:54,133 --> 00:07:57,533
Coleen, let's not get
ahead of ourselves.

170
00:07:57,667 --> 00:07:59,900
There's still Jeffrey
and Andrea.

171
00:08:00,033 --> 00:08:02,567
That's another fight.

172
00:08:02,700 --> 00:08:04,667
Dear, your sister is right.

173
00:08:06,267 --> 00:08:08,433
We still need to leave.

174
00:08:08,567 --> 00:08:10,533
Where would you go?

175
00:08:14,067 --> 00:08:18,733
We saw an apartment for rent
on a FriendsBook page.

176
00:08:18,867 --> 00:08:19,767
It's a bit pricey,

177
00:08:19,900 --> 00:08:22,867
but dad and I are still thinking
about it.

178
00:08:32,833 --> 00:08:33,600
Let me in

179
00:08:33,733 --> 00:08:34,367
- because I need to talk...
- Ma'am,

180
00:08:34,500 --> 00:08:35,900
you're causing trouble again!

181
00:08:36,033 --> 00:08:36,800
Causing trouble?

182
00:08:36,933 --> 00:08:38,133
They're not here.

183
00:08:38,267 --> 00:08:39,400
I don't believe you.

184
00:08:39,533 --> 00:08:41,100
- Give me the owner's number.
- Ma'am.

185
00:08:41,233 --> 00:08:42,867
I'll call myself
because you're useless!

186
00:08:43,000 --> 00:08:44,100
What now?

187
00:08:44,233 --> 00:08:45,467
- I said give it to me, or else.
- Ma'am, I can't do that.

188
00:08:45,600 --> 00:08:46,567
No!

189
00:08:46,700 --> 00:08:47,833
Get out of my way!

190
00:08:47,967 --> 00:08:49,300
- I need to see...
- Ma'am, that's not allowed!

191
00:08:49,433 --> 00:08:50,533
What do you mean not allowed?

192
00:08:50,667 --> 00:08:52,367
What do you mean I can't?
Don't you understand?

193
00:08:52,500 --> 00:08:55,433
- This is important...
- Excuse me, excuse me.

194
00:08:55,600 --> 00:08:57,167
Rudy,

195
00:08:57,300 --> 00:08:59,367
is this the woman who caused
a scene here last night?

196
00:08:59,500 --> 00:09:00,833
Yes, Ma'am.

197
00:09:00,967 --> 00:09:01,867
And who are you?

198
00:09:03,100 --> 00:09:04,733
I'm the unit owner.

199
00:09:04,867 --> 00:09:09,633
So, can you not act like
you own the whole building?

200
00:09:09,767 --> 00:09:11,667
My child was kidnapped.

201
00:09:11,800 --> 00:09:13,067
By Manuel.

202
00:09:13,200 --> 00:09:15,567
She's a minor. Am I not
supposed to lose my mind?

203
00:09:18,533 --> 00:09:20,733
You mean that kind,
paralyzed guy?

204
00:09:20,867 --> 00:09:22,767
Doesn't really seem like
a kidnapper to me.

205
00:09:22,900 --> 00:09:26,733
As far as I know,
he's Jessica's father.

206
00:09:26,867 --> 00:09:28,300
And he's my husband.

207
00:09:29,767 --> 00:09:31,167
You want a proof?

208
00:09:31,300 --> 00:09:32,267
Here.

209
00:09:34,900 --> 00:09:37,233
Our family photo.

210
00:09:37,367 --> 00:09:39,233
What now? Want more evidence?

211
00:09:39,367 --> 00:09:41,700
So I can shove it
right in your face?

212
00:09:43,533 --> 00:09:44,733
What?

213
00:09:44,867 --> 00:09:46,767
Lost your attitude now?

214
00:09:47,933 --> 00:09:48,967
You know what?

215
00:09:50,833 --> 00:09:54,067
You could be charged as an
accessory to my husband's crime.

216
00:09:54,200 --> 00:09:56,833
Maybe you're even involved.

217
00:09:56,967 --> 00:10:01,667
What if you're an accomplice
in the kidnapping of my child?

218
00:10:01,833 --> 00:10:02,633
What?

219
00:10:02,767 --> 00:10:04,567
Yes.

220
00:10:04,700 --> 00:10:07,433
So if you don't do what I say,

221
00:10:07,567 --> 00:10:10,067
I'll make sure
to implicate you in the case.

222
00:10:10,200 --> 00:10:11,933
Especially you.

223
00:10:56,500 --> 00:10:58,200
Miss Hazel?

224
00:11:06,033 --> 00:11:08,667
I'm sorry for...

225
00:11:08,833 --> 00:11:11,067
scaring you...

226
00:11:11,200 --> 00:11:13,233
just to get in here.

227
00:11:14,700 --> 00:11:15,667
The truth is...

228
00:11:16,933 --> 00:11:18,067
I'm desperate.

229
00:11:19,900 --> 00:11:22,033
I'm broken.

230
00:11:22,167 --> 00:11:24,800
I was just pretending
to be strong earlier.

231
00:11:26,533 --> 00:11:29,100
Please, don't get me wrong.

232
00:11:30,300 --> 00:11:32,067
I'm not a bad person.

233
00:11:34,433 --> 00:11:36,133
I love my husband.

234
00:11:37,900 --> 00:11:39,767
But he wants to leave me...

235
00:11:39,900 --> 00:11:41,467
for another woman.

236
00:11:45,167 --> 00:11:46,733
And what hurts even more...

237
00:11:48,033 --> 00:11:50,667
he brainwashed our child,

238
00:11:50,800 --> 00:11:51,933
and took her with him.

239
00:12:03,067 --> 00:12:04,900
I'm sorry to hear that.

240
00:12:07,167 --> 00:12:09,567
I know I made mistakes, too.

241
00:12:10,667 --> 00:12:12,733
But maybe...

242
00:12:12,867 --> 00:12:14,900
I deserve a second chance.

243
00:12:16,667 --> 00:12:18,933
I need my family's forgiveness.

244
00:12:19,967 --> 00:12:21,733
I want my family back.

245
00:12:23,667 --> 00:12:27,033
Please, please, help me.

246
00:12:27,167 --> 00:12:28,133
Please.

247
00:12:30,467 --> 00:12:32,267
How?

248
00:12:32,400 --> 00:12:34,633
Let me stay here.

249
00:12:34,767 --> 00:12:38,400
If you'll allow me,
let me wait for them.

250
00:12:38,533 --> 00:12:40,467
Okay.

251
00:12:40,600 --> 00:12:42,167
- Really?
- Yes.

252
00:12:42,300 --> 00:12:46,333
But what if...

253
00:12:46,467 --> 00:12:48,067
they call you?

254
00:12:48,233 --> 00:12:51,000
The guard might kick me out.

255
00:12:51,133 --> 00:12:55,333
I'll help you. I'll explain
the situation to them. Okay?

256
00:12:55,467 --> 00:12:56,967
Really?

257
00:12:59,233 --> 00:13:00,233
Thank you so much.

258
00:13:09,367 --> 00:13:11,667
<i> That was easy.</i>

259
00:13:11,800 --> 00:13:14,300
<i>People are so easy
to manipulate.</i>

260
00:13:26,067 --> 00:13:28,600
Coleen, stay there for now.

261
00:13:28,733 --> 00:13:30,567
Your mom's still here.

262
00:13:30,700 --> 00:13:32,833
- Didang.
- Ma'am?

263
00:13:32,967 --> 00:13:34,000
Can you put this on a plate?

264
00:13:34,133 --> 00:13:37,633
I'll bring this
to Coleen's room.

265
00:13:37,767 --> 00:13:38,900
Oh, no need, Ma'am.

266
00:13:39,033 --> 00:13:40,000
You already cooked.

267
00:13:40,133 --> 00:13:40,900
It's okay, I'll take care of it.

268
00:13:41,033 --> 00:13:42,267
I'll be the one to bring it.

269
00:13:42,400 --> 00:13:43,733
Yeah.

270
00:13:43,867 --> 00:13:45,400
I'll just put it here.

271
00:13:45,533 --> 00:13:48,000
Didang, I've been
noticing something...

272
00:13:48,133 --> 00:13:49,867
You've been tense
for a while now.

273
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:51,600
You're hiding something,
aren't you?

274
00:13:51,733 --> 00:13:53,733
Ma'am, please, I'm not.

275
00:13:53,867 --> 00:13:56,167
Tell me the truth.

276
00:13:56,333 --> 00:13:57,400
There's nothing.

277
00:13:57,533 --> 00:13:58,200
Didang...

278
00:14:01,367 --> 00:14:03,500
Coleen, why'd you come
from the back?

279
00:14:03,633 --> 00:14:06,467
Weren't you feeling unwell?

280
00:14:09,533 --> 00:14:11,433
I'm feeling better now, Mom.

281
00:14:11,567 --> 00:14:12,867
I just checked something
in the laundry.

282
00:14:13,000 --> 00:14:16,100
My ID was in my uniform.

283
00:14:16,233 --> 00:14:17,967
Oh, I saw that.

284
00:14:18,100 --> 00:14:22,500
I took it and put it
on your table upstairs.

285
00:14:22,633 --> 00:14:24,700
- Okay.
- I already placed it there.

286
00:14:24,833 --> 00:14:27,500
Oh, I'll just eat here.

287
00:14:27,633 --> 00:14:28,800
Okay, sure.

288
00:14:28,967 --> 00:14:29,700
Okay.

289
00:14:29,833 --> 00:14:30,900
I'll join you.

290
00:14:31,033 --> 00:14:32,433
Let's talk.

291
00:14:32,567 --> 00:14:34,400
And I'll be the one to take you
to school.

292
00:14:34,533 --> 00:14:35,600
No, Mom, it's fine.

293
00:14:35,733 --> 00:14:37,633
You go ahead.

294
00:14:37,767 --> 00:14:38,967
No.

295
00:14:39,100 --> 00:14:40,300
I'll take you to school.

296
00:14:41,800 --> 00:14:44,200
All right, I'll wait
for you at the table.

297
00:14:56,900 --> 00:14:58,200
Please come in.

298
00:14:58,333 --> 00:14:59,300
Please close the door.

299
00:14:59,433 --> 00:15:01,200
Sorry.

300
00:15:01,367 --> 00:15:04,233
I had to grab some rice
so I could bring you this food.

301
00:15:04,367 --> 00:15:06,100
- Thank you.
- Thanks, Didang.

302
00:15:06,233 --> 00:15:07,567
It's nothing, really.

303
00:15:10,733 --> 00:15:12,600
Too bad Coleen isn't here.

304
00:15:12,733 --> 00:15:15,933
I was really looking forward
to eat breakfast with her.

305
00:15:16,067 --> 00:15:18,133
She's feeling down too.

306
00:15:18,267 --> 00:15:21,367
But of course,
she can't really show it.

307
00:15:21,500 --> 00:15:23,433
Ma'am Felma might
notice something's up.

308
00:15:23,567 --> 00:15:24,433
All right then.

309
00:15:24,567 --> 00:15:26,067
Go ahead and eat.

310
00:15:33,133 --> 00:15:35,267
You know, Didang...

311
00:15:35,433 --> 00:15:39,300
only Felma can cook
longganisa this good.

312
00:15:39,433 --> 00:15:40,367
I really miss it.

313
00:15:40,500 --> 00:15:42,233
Ma'am Felma?

314
00:15:42,367 --> 00:15:43,633
You miss her?

315
00:15:43,767 --> 00:15:45,867
No, the longganisa.

316
00:15:48,067 --> 00:15:50,700
It would've been nicer
if we were with...

317
00:15:50,833 --> 00:15:51,933
Ma'am Felma?

318
00:15:52,067 --> 00:15:54,267
There, did I guess it right?

319
00:15:54,400 --> 00:15:55,667
It's Coleen!

320
00:15:55,800 --> 00:15:57,733
What are you talking about,
Didang?

321
00:15:57,867 --> 00:15:58,767
You're such a gossipmonger!

322
00:15:58,900 --> 00:15:59,833
Come on, Sir Manuel.

323
00:15:59,967 --> 00:16:00,867
I was just teasing you.

324
00:16:01,000 --> 00:16:03,233
Oh, wait, I forgot your drinks!

325
00:16:03,367 --> 00:16:04,633
I'll be right back, okay?

326
00:16:04,767 --> 00:16:05,533
Thank you!

327
00:16:05,667 --> 00:16:06,767
Okay, thank you.

328
00:16:17,633 --> 00:16:19,300
When they get here,

329
00:16:19,433 --> 00:16:22,600
I'll drag them to the airport
if I have to.

330
00:16:22,733 --> 00:16:27,067
<i>Friend, congratulations
on tricking the unit owner</i>

331
00:16:27,200 --> 00:16:28,667
<i> into letting you stay.</i>

332
00:16:28,800 --> 00:16:30,400
But what now?

333
00:16:30,533 --> 00:16:33,233
Are you just going to sit there
and wait?

334
00:16:33,367 --> 00:16:36,900
I don't think Manuel and Jessica
are coming back.

335
00:16:37,033 --> 00:16:41,733
<i>They left everything behind,
documents, passports, even cash.</i>

336
00:16:41,900 --> 00:16:43,800
That's why I'm sure
they'll come back.

337
00:16:43,933 --> 00:16:48,167
<i>But if you're right that
Felma helped them escape,</i>

338
00:16:48,300 --> 00:16:50,967
she can cover everything.

339
00:16:51,100 --> 00:16:53,000
She's got money.

340
00:16:53,133 --> 00:16:56,400
<i> So you need a Plan B.</i>

341
00:16:56,533 --> 00:16:58,233
Oh, yeah.

342
00:16:58,367 --> 00:16:59,800
You're right.

343
00:16:59,933 --> 00:17:01,933
All right, I'll call you later,
okay?

344
00:17:24,467 --> 00:17:25,500
Oh, I know!

345
00:17:25,633 --> 00:17:26,800
Buy some palabok

346
00:17:26,933 --> 00:17:28,033
- for the meeting.
- Palabok.

347
00:17:28,167 --> 00:17:30,867
Palabok. Because it's Jeff
and Andeng's favorite, okay?

348
00:17:31,000 --> 00:17:32,767
- All right, go ahead and order.
- Okay, I'm ordering now.

349
00:17:32,900 --> 00:17:33,567
All right.

350
00:17:38,533 --> 00:17:39,600
Good morning.

351
00:17:41,367 --> 00:17:45,367
Oh no, no one's
at the reception.

352
00:17:45,500 --> 00:17:46,500
Hello!

353
00:17:46,633 --> 00:17:49,367
Juicy morning, FMP buddy!

354
00:17:49,533 --> 00:17:51,833
Felma's Meat Products, hello?

355
00:17:51,967 --> 00:17:53,467
May I speak to the owner?

356
00:17:53,600 --> 00:17:55,233
<i> Miss Felma Ruiz?</i>

357
00:17:55,367 --> 00:17:57,500
Hazel, you troublemaker!

358
00:17:57,633 --> 00:17:58,633
I recognize your voice.

359
00:17:58,767 --> 00:17:59,833
Why are you calling here?

360
00:18:04,700 --> 00:18:06,500
I'm sorry, Ma'am.

361
00:18:06,633 --> 00:18:07,967
Who's Hazel?

362
00:18:08,100 --> 00:18:10,433
This is Stephanie Lim
from Value More.

363
00:18:13,333 --> 00:18:14,700
Value More, you say?

364
00:18:14,833 --> 00:18:15,833
Sorry, Ma'am.

365
00:18:15,967 --> 00:18:17,400
I thought you were...

366
00:18:17,533 --> 00:18:18,167
Never mind.

367
00:18:18,300 --> 00:18:20,600
At your service, yes?

368
00:18:20,733 --> 00:18:23,167
Yes, Ma'am. I'm the PR head.

369
00:18:23,333 --> 00:18:27,233
We would like to send
a VIP invite to Miss Felma Ruiz

370
00:18:27,367 --> 00:18:29,000
for our upcoming event.

371
00:18:29,133 --> 00:18:31,767
May I ask for her home address?

372
00:18:32,800 --> 00:18:35,200
Please just send it
to the office.

373
00:18:35,333 --> 00:18:36,233
<i> I'm sorry, Ma'am.</i>

374
00:18:36,367 --> 00:18:38,067
We really wanted to deliver it
to her house

375
00:18:38,200 --> 00:18:39,833
to make sure she gets it.

376
00:18:39,967 --> 00:18:42,633
Because it includes 10,000 worth
of gift certificates

377
00:18:42,767 --> 00:18:43,967
from Value More.

378
00:18:44,100 --> 00:18:50,233
And also, we have a VIP invite
and card for Miss Paz Antonio.

379
00:18:50,367 --> 00:18:51,567
That's me, that's me!

380
00:18:51,700 --> 00:18:53,167
Did you say there's
a gift certificate?

381
00:18:53,300 --> 00:18:55,233
Do I get one too?

382
00:18:55,400 --> 00:18:56,533
Yes, of course.

383
00:18:56,667 --> 00:19:00,433
10,000 worth of gift
certificates from Value More.

384
00:19:00,567 --> 00:19:01,600
Get your pen and paper.

385
00:19:01,733 --> 00:19:05,000
I'll dictate our addresses
to you, okay?

386
00:19:16,200 --> 00:19:17,500
Thank you very much, Didang.

387
00:19:17,633 --> 00:19:20,233
Oh, you're always welcome.

388
00:19:20,367 --> 00:19:21,467
You know, Jessica,

389
00:19:21,600 --> 00:19:24,867
that hand-me-down clothes
from Coleen really suit you.

390
00:19:25,000 --> 00:19:26,800
It's actually pretty cute.

391
00:19:26,933 --> 00:19:28,267
By the way, where's Coleen?

392
00:19:28,400 --> 00:19:31,567
They are about to leave.

393
00:19:33,100 --> 00:19:35,000
We couldn't even say goodbye.

394
00:19:36,000 --> 00:19:37,833
Coleen wanted to come here, too,

395
00:19:37,967 --> 00:19:42,100
but Ma'am Felma
wouldn't leave her side.

396
00:19:43,667 --> 00:19:46,100
Looks like you really
liked Ma'am Felma...

397
00:19:46,233 --> 00:19:49,600
I mean the longganisa, Sir.

398
00:19:49,733 --> 00:19:51,067
You're so silly, Didang.

399
00:19:51,200 --> 00:19:53,000
I'll be back for snacks later.

400
00:20:01,667 --> 00:20:05,733
Why are you bringing that?
Shouldn't it be Didang?

401
00:20:05,867 --> 00:20:06,933
- It's okay, Mom.
- Come on.

402
00:20:07,067 --> 00:20:08,133
Didang is busy.

403
00:20:08,267 --> 00:20:11,167
Oh, Didang.

404
00:20:11,300 --> 00:20:12,300
Felma!

405
00:20:14,433 --> 00:20:15,400
Felma, you're such a flirt.

406
00:20:16,400 --> 00:20:18,767
Bring out Manuel and Jessica!

407
00:20:18,900 --> 00:20:20,800
How did you even get in here?

408
00:20:26,800 --> 00:20:28,167
That's good.

409
00:20:31,933 --> 00:20:33,133
Andrea, how's it going?

410
00:20:33,267 --> 00:20:34,367
Yes.

411
00:20:34,500 --> 00:20:36,367
The attendees are on their way.
They'll be here in a bit.

412
00:20:36,533 --> 00:20:38,267
But Felma's not here yet.

413
00:20:38,400 --> 00:20:39,967
Maybe she's stuck in traffic.

414
00:20:40,100 --> 00:20:42,533
She messaged me earlier. She
said she's dropping off Coleen.

415
00:20:42,667 --> 00:20:45,233
But she knows there's a meeting
today, right?

416
00:20:45,367 --> 00:20:50,600
Well, honestly, Auntie,
Coleen's upset.

417
00:20:50,733 --> 00:20:54,667
So mom's trying to coax her.

418
00:20:54,800 --> 00:20:56,933
It's because we all scolded her.

419
00:20:57,067 --> 00:20:58,367
What?

420
00:20:58,500 --> 00:20:59,900
Why? What happened?

421
00:21:01,267 --> 00:21:04,767
Coleen went to see her dad.

422
00:21:05,700 --> 00:21:08,500
So, mom scolded her...

423
00:21:08,667 --> 00:21:09,900
all of us did.

424
00:21:11,800 --> 00:21:15,500
You're all fighting again
because of Manuel.

425
00:21:15,633 --> 00:21:18,733
That man really won't leave
you alone.

426
00:21:18,867 --> 00:21:21,200
I'll just call your mom, okay?

427
00:21:21,333 --> 00:21:23,033
I don't believe it. Manuel!

428
00:21:23,167 --> 00:21:23,667
Hazel!

429
00:21:23,800 --> 00:21:24,733
- Hazel!
- Jessica!

430
00:21:24,867 --> 00:21:25,867
What's wrong with you?
They're not even here!

431
00:21:26,000 --> 00:21:27,033
Manuel, Jessica!

432
00:21:27,167 --> 00:21:28,567
How many times do I have to say
that they're not here?

433
00:21:28,700 --> 00:21:30,067
- Just stop it already!
- Get out of here!

434
00:21:30,200 --> 00:21:32,233
You have no right
to get inside my house!

435
00:21:32,367 --> 00:21:33,567
- Oh, is that so?
- Coleen! Coleen!

436
00:21:33,700 --> 00:21:34,867
- Call the guard house!
- Okay.

437
00:21:35,000 --> 00:21:36,000
I know they're here!

438
00:21:36,133 --> 00:21:38,733
They really aren't here,
so just stop it!

439
00:21:38,867 --> 00:21:41,567
Thank you so much
for everything, Didang.

440
00:21:41,700 --> 00:21:43,967
Please take care of Coleen.

441
00:21:44,133 --> 00:21:47,200
Don't worry about that.

442
00:21:47,333 --> 00:21:49,600
I'll be the one to see you out.

443
00:21:49,733 --> 00:21:53,433
I'll just make sure Ma'am Felma
has already left.

444
00:21:53,567 --> 00:21:57,000
I've also prepared
a quick exit route for you.

445
00:21:57,133 --> 00:21:58,800
- Let's go.
- Thank you.

446
00:22:01,033 --> 00:22:03,267
<i>Okay! I'm going to sue you
for trespassing!</i>

447
00:22:03,400 --> 00:22:05,667
- I'll sue you for kidnapping.
- What's that?

448
00:22:05,800 --> 00:22:07,000
Do you hear that?

449
00:22:07,133 --> 00:22:09,400
<i>You'll only feel ashamed
because they're not here!</i>

450
00:22:11,667 --> 00:22:13,000
Dad!

451
00:22:13,133 --> 00:22:14,700
Your wife is outside!

452
00:22:14,833 --> 00:22:16,100
- What?
- My mom?

453
00:22:16,267 --> 00:22:17,400
Yes.

454
00:22:17,533 --> 00:22:18,800
How did she know we're here?

455
00:22:18,933 --> 00:22:20,767
I don't think she knows.

456
00:22:20,900 --> 00:22:22,400
Sounds like she's just bluffing.

457
00:22:22,533 --> 00:22:24,100
You need to hide.

458
00:22:24,233 --> 00:22:25,700
No, I'm going to face Hazel.

459
00:22:25,833 --> 00:22:27,233
Felma needs help.

460
00:22:27,367 --> 00:22:29,967
Mom can't see you, Dad.

461
00:22:30,100 --> 00:22:32,867
I'll take care of her.
I'm the one who'll help her.

462
00:22:33,000 --> 00:22:34,333
Didang, I'll leave them to you.

463
00:22:34,467 --> 00:22:36,067
- Okay.
- Also call the guardhouse.

464
00:22:36,200 --> 00:22:37,000
All right, I'll do that.

465
00:22:37,133 --> 00:22:39,133
Okay, I'll go back to mom now.

466
00:22:43,100 --> 00:22:44,400
Follow me, okay?

467
00:22:44,533 --> 00:22:46,133
Let's go through
the dirty kitchen.

468
00:22:46,267 --> 00:22:47,233
Come on.

469
00:22:47,367 --> 00:22:49,000
Slowly, okay?

470
00:22:49,167 --> 00:22:50,533
Let's go.

471
00:22:59,300 --> 00:23:02,500
She's not answering.
I'll just text her.

472
00:23:02,633 --> 00:23:05,633
Andrea, call Didang.
I'll call Coleen.

473
00:23:05,767 --> 00:23:06,800
Okay.

474
00:23:13,600 --> 00:23:14,467
- Manuel!
- You're shameless!

475
00:23:14,600 --> 00:23:15,533
- Jessica!
- You have no right

476
00:23:15,667 --> 00:23:17,033
to enter my home!

477
00:23:17,167 --> 00:23:18,033
What are you doing?

478
00:23:18,167 --> 00:23:19,900
Go ahead,
I'll sue you for trespassing!

479
00:23:20,033 --> 00:23:21,300
And I'll sue you for kidnapping!

480
00:23:21,433 --> 00:23:22,900
- No!
- Manuel!

481
00:23:23,067 --> 00:23:24,933
They're not here!
You'll embarrass yourself!

482
00:23:25,067 --> 00:23:26,967
- You can even bring your...
- Manuel!

483
00:23:27,100 --> 00:23:29,567
What are you going to do to me?
Throw me in the pool?

484
00:23:29,700 --> 00:23:31,233
- Wow, that's so original.
- No!

485
00:23:31,367 --> 00:23:34,633
I won't let my pool get dirty
because of you!

486
00:23:34,767 --> 00:23:35,900
This! This!

487
00:23:36,033 --> 00:23:37,967
This one's for you!

488
00:23:38,100 --> 00:23:38,700
Take that!

489
00:23:38,833 --> 00:23:40,600
That's for you!

490
00:23:40,733 --> 00:23:42,467
Didang's not answering.

491
00:23:42,600 --> 00:23:43,833
Coleen, too.

492
00:23:45,500 --> 00:23:47,300
Listen.

493
00:23:47,433 --> 00:23:50,033
When our meeting
attendees arrive,

494
00:23:50,167 --> 00:23:52,167
we'll proceed with the meeting.

495
00:23:52,300 --> 00:23:54,933
And when Felma arrives,

496
00:23:55,100 --> 00:23:56,800
she can just catch up.

497
00:23:56,933 --> 00:23:58,667
We have a lot to discuss.

498
00:23:58,800 --> 00:23:59,933
All right.

499
00:24:06,233 --> 00:24:07,100
What now?

500
00:24:07,233 --> 00:24:08,933
That's it!
That suits you perfectly!

501
00:24:09,067 --> 00:24:09,967
Mom!

502
00:24:10,100 --> 00:24:11,133
Shameless witch!

503
00:24:11,267 --> 00:24:13,000
- Mom!
- Shameless witch!

504
00:24:13,133 --> 00:24:14,700
- Mom, stop it, please!
- Hazel, you witch!

505
00:24:14,833 --> 00:24:16,333
- Don't stoop to her level.
- Coleen.

506
00:24:16,467 --> 00:24:18,200
- Mom, please! That's enough.
- No, Coleen.

507
00:24:21,700 --> 00:24:23,400
Not my daughter!

508
00:24:24,967 --> 00:24:26,633
Darn you!

509
00:24:29,533 --> 00:24:32,700
Let go of Ma'am Felma!

510
00:24:32,833 --> 00:24:34,633
Won't you really stop?

511
00:24:34,767 --> 00:24:36,733
Manuel, get out of there!

512
00:24:36,867 --> 00:24:38,633
- They're not here!
- Jessica!

513
00:24:38,767 --> 00:24:41,333
Get out of here!

514
00:24:41,467 --> 00:24:42,433
Didang!

515
00:24:42,567 --> 00:24:43,533
Didang!

516
00:24:43,667 --> 00:24:44,900
- What are you going to do?
- Leave her to me!

517
00:24:45,033 --> 00:24:45,900
What will you do?

518
00:24:46,033 --> 00:24:47,767
You're way out of line!

519
00:24:47,900 --> 00:24:49,467
I've been trying to stop you!

520
00:24:49,600 --> 00:24:51,333
You don't want to be stopped!

521
00:24:51,467 --> 00:24:53,733
Dear, you're hurt.

522
00:24:53,867 --> 00:24:54,967
Dear.

523
00:24:55,100 --> 00:24:56,967
Dear, you're hurt.

524
00:24:59,500 --> 00:25:01,200
Get lost!

525
00:25:01,333 --> 00:25:02,667
- Leave!
- Stop it!

526
00:25:04,333 --> 00:25:05,067
Leave!

527
00:25:07,233 --> 00:25:08,300
Darn you.

528
00:25:08,433 --> 00:25:09,667
I'll come after you!

529
00:25:09,800 --> 00:25:11,467
Until I get my family back!

530
00:25:11,600 --> 00:25:13,900
- Get lost!
- Jessica! Manuel!

531
00:25:14,033 --> 00:25:14,833
- Leave!
- Get out!

532
00:25:14,967 --> 00:25:15,833
Leave!

533
00:25:19,267 --> 00:25:19,900
Leave!

534
00:25:20,033 --> 00:25:21,333
Dear, are you okay?

535
00:25:21,467 --> 00:25:23,333
Are you okay, Mom?

536
00:25:23,467 --> 00:25:25,733
I'm okay.

537
00:25:25,867 --> 00:25:26,467
Didang.

538
00:25:26,600 --> 00:25:27,600
Didang, come here.

539
00:25:27,733 --> 00:25:28,433
Coleen.

540
00:25:28,567 --> 00:25:30,100
Let's bring her to the hospital.

541
00:25:30,233 --> 00:25:31,233
Coleen!

542
00:25:31,367 --> 00:25:33,167
So, that's how much you are.

543
00:25:33,300 --> 00:25:34,867
You're so cheap!

544
00:25:35,867 --> 00:25:37,667
You little devil, Hazel!
Just wait and see!

545
00:25:37,800 --> 00:25:39,667
Why are you talking
to Manuel's wife?

546
00:25:39,800 --> 00:25:41,967
Let's just forget
about the problems for now.

547
00:25:42,100 --> 00:25:43,733
Hey, what do you have in mind?

548
00:25:43,867 --> 00:25:45,533
I'm sneaking in tonight

549
00:25:45,667 --> 00:25:47,867
so we can sleep next
to each other.

550
00:25:48,000 --> 00:25:49,533
I'd love that!

551
00:25:49,667 --> 00:25:51,333
Let's get down to business.

552
00:25:51,467 --> 00:25:53,600
Your timing is perfect,
classmate.

553
00:25:53,733 --> 00:25:56,300
I want you to find them.

554
00:25:56,433 --> 00:25:57,700
Find these two.

555
00:25:57,833 --> 00:25:59,200
- Didang.
- They all left.

556
00:25:59,333 --> 00:26:00,700
Have you already booked a ride?

557
00:26:00,833 --> 00:26:02,300
Yes, it's already
waiting outside.

558
00:26:02,433 --> 00:26:05,367
Okay. Go. Be safe, okay?

559
00:26:05,500 --> 00:26:06,700
Jessica?

560
00:26:06,833 --> 00:26:07,633
Jessica!

561
00:26:07,767 --> 00:26:10,233
Why do you have so much food?

562
00:26:10,400 --> 00:26:13,100
I'm planning to eat
in the laundry area.

563
00:26:13,233 --> 00:26:15,667
I'd like to eat
while doing the laundry.

564
00:26:15,800 --> 00:26:16,700
Didang.

565
00:26:17,900 --> 00:26:20,867
Was that Jessica I saw earlier?
